# Blurb for the Apps For America official submission.

Plaster a congressional info-poster across any webpage.

# And the long-form...

Say you're reading a newspaper article online and you come across an interesting 
quote from an unfamiliar senator. (Happens to me all the time.) To learn more 
about them, highlight a name and click on the Know Thy Congressman bookmarklet. 
You'll bring up a detailed display with all the dirt on that legislator: 
earmarks requested, bills introduced, contact information, photos of, articles 
concerning, and so on. An informed citizenry is the bulwark of democracy; 
know thy congressman, know thyself.